        "content": "# GOOG \u2014 Technicals\n\n## TL;DR\n\nThe most recent run (20260415_093758, April 15 2026) shows GOOG executing a textbook breakout above the daily resistance at $330.58. Daily ADX of 37 and hourly ADX of 80 jointly confirm a strong, real trend on both timeframes. Both timeframes are simultaneously overbought, so the ideal entry is on a pullback retest of $327\u2013330 rather than chasing at $332.\n\n## Multi-timeframe state\n\n**Daily (as of April 15, 2026):**\n- RSI: 77.1 \u2014 overbought, confirmed uptrend\n- MACD histogram: +4.87 \u2014 largest positive value of any ticker in the April 15 basket; expanding\n- ADX: 37.1 \u2014 trend confirmed (above 25 threshold)\n- Supertrend: bullish\n- Squeeze Momentum: bullish breakout, momentum 17.49 and increasing\n- Bollinger Band position: 0.999 \u2014 price touching the upper band; near-term consolidation probable\n- Z-score: 1.61 \u2014 approaching formal overbought statistical threshold\n- ROC: +8.77% (5d), +21.03% (10d), +9.66% (21d) \u2014 second-strongest momentum in April 15 universe\n\n**Hourly (as of April 15, 2026):**\n- ADX: 79.9 \u2014 exceptionally strong intraday trend\n- RSI: 82 \u2014 overbought on the intraday frame\n- EMA structure: fully aligned uptrend\n- STC: overbought\n- Supertrend: bullish, distance +1.68%\n\nSource: 20260415_093758 signals \u2014 swing_trend_follower, swing_momentum_ranker, swing_breakout_trader agent outputs for GOOG.\n\n## Key levels\n\n| Level | Value | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| Breakout resistance (now support) | $330.58 | Cleared April 14; 20260415 breakout agent |\n| Pullback retest zone | $327\u2013330 | Fib 23.6% at $327.78; ideal entry per catalyst + pullback agents |\n| Prior swing high / target 1 | $342\u2013344 | Breakout + trend agents' target |\n| Extended target | $355 | Momentum ranker and PM target (20260415 decisions.json) |\n| Stop loss | $318\u2013321 | Swing trend stop $321; PM stop $318 |\n| Invalidation | Below $318 | Closes below stop; thesis abandoned |\n\n## Setup type\n\nConfirmed breakout with multi-timeframe trend alignment. Both daily and hourly overbought simultaneously is the primary risk \u2014 enter only on intraday pullback to $327\u2013330 retest, not on open at $332+. If the stock consolidates sideways for 1\u20132 days without breaking $326, that is acceptable digestion before continuation.\n\n## Last updated\n\nData from run 20260415_093758 (April 15, 2026). Stale after 7 days \u2014 rerun model before any new entry decision.\n",
